<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648498>
    dc:description "Figures 23–35: Figure 23. Distribution of Isometrus kovariki sp. n. Figures 24–27: Comparison of pedipalp movable finger dentition. Figures 28–31: Comparison of telson in ventral view. Figures 32–35: Comparison of metasoma II–III in lateral view. Figures 24, 28, 32. I. kovariki sp. n., male, holotype. Figures 25, 29, 33. I. thurstoni, male, INHER-SC-139. Figures 26, 30, 34. I. tamhini, male, holotype. Figures 27, 31, 35. I. amboli, male, holotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648498/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648490>
    dc:description "Figures 2–6. Isometrus kovariki sp. n., male holotype, dorsal (2) and ventral (3) views, sternopectinal area (4), telson in lateral view (5) and chelicera in dorsal view (6)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648490/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648494>
    dc:description "Figures 9–11. Isometrus kovariki sp. n., female, paratype, BNHS SC 162, in dorsal (9) and ventral (10) views, and sternopectinal area (11)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648494/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648496>
    dc:description "Figures 12–22: Isometrus kovariki sp. n. Figures 12–18, 20. Male, holotype, pedipalp chela dorsoexternal (12) and ventral (13), patella dorsal (14) and external (15), and femur dorsal (16) and internal (17) views. Trichobothrial pattern indicated by yellow circles. Carapace under white light (18) and UV fluorescence (20). Figures 19, 21. Female, paratype, BNHS SC 162, carapace under white light (19) and UV fluorescence (21). Figure 22. Type locality, a view of dense plantation with tall trees." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648496/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648492>
    dc:description "Figures 7–8. Isometrus kovariki sp. n., male holotype in dorsal (7) and ventral (8) views under UV fluorescence." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648492/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

